{
  "_id": "fhSubRflxInjct01",
  "name": "Reflex Injector",
  "type": "consumable",
  "img": "icons/svg/item-bag.svg",
  "folder": "fhSubSciFi000001",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A spring-loaded combat injector preloaded with synthetic adrenocortical accelerant. Strapped to the thigh, deployed under fire. Brand-name stocks are mil-spec; the gray-market versions occasionally crystallize.</p><p><strong><em>Desired effects on use.</em></strong> For 1 minute you have a +2 bonus to Dexterity (initiative is rolled with this bonus if used as a reaction at the start of combat) and your walking speed increases by 10 feet.</p><p><strong><em>On use, save against addiction.</em></strong> Make a DC 15 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, you gain the Addicted condition from Reflex Injector (see below).</p><p><strong><em>Addicted from Reflex Injector.</em></strong> While you have this Addicted condition, you are also Poisoned, have disadvantage on saving throws against being frightened, and your walking speed is reduced by 5 feet.</p><p><strong><em>Withdrawal Modifier: 5.</em></strong> Withdrawal lasts max(5 &minus; your Constitution modifier, 3) long rests, minimum 1.</p><p><em>Requires: Syringe.</em></p>"
    },
